<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">📖 Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">Today the work moves from "practicing OPVL" to "doing OPVL on YOUR question."</p>
  <p>Up to now, OPVL has been a framework you've watched and tried on practice sources. Today you pick a topic from the released contested-topic list, conference briefly with Mr. Ignash to lock it, and start building your <a href="/units/unit-0/assessment-source-dossier/">Source Dossier</a>. Two traditional sources today, AI source tomorrow.</p>
  <p>"Traditional" here means "not generative AI" — a textbook chapter, a news article, an interview, a peer-reviewed paper, a primary document. The contrast matters: by separating traditional sources today from the AI source tomorrow, you can feel the differences in what OPVL reveals about each. The same four questions; very different answers.</p>
</section>

