<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">🛠️ Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">Conferencing with Mr. Ignash happens in the first 15 minutes; research runs the middle 50; peer-check closes the block. The path you pick is about where you are with your topic.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I can lock my Source Dossier topic and complete OPVL on at least one traditional source by end of class.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Topic lock + first source OPVL</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Brief teacher conference to lock your topic. Then find one traditional source (textbook, news, or peer-reviewed). Complete OPVL on it. Start the second.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Two-source OPVL (topic already chosen)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If you locked your topic early, go straight to research. Two traditional sources, OPVL completed on both. Aim for sources that take different angles on the same question.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Source-hunting on a hard topic</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If your topic is genuinely contested (5G health claims, GMO safety), finding strong traditional sources is part of the work. Spend the block on source-hunting; aim for one solid OPVL by end of class.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Choice</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Peer-help station</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Stuck on OPVL on a tricky source? Come to the peer-help table. Two students who finished Source 1 take turns walking each other through it. Mr. Ignash floats. Capacity ~6 at a time.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Pairs · Practice</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

